      "message": "yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Common.events.yaml\nversion: 1.0.0\nerrors:\n     name: ObjectAlreadyExists\n      severity: warning\n      errno: EEXIST\n      metadata:\n           name: ObjectPath\n            description: The path of the existing object that conflicts with the requested creation.\n            type: object_path\n            primary: true\n      en:\n          description: The object already exists under the given object manager.\n          message: \"Object already exists at \u0027{ObjectPath}\u0027.\"\n\nI\u0027ve moved the new error over to Common.events.yaml as suggested.\n\nFor context, here\u0027s what changed on the generation side to support that:\ngen/xyz/openbmc_project/Common/meson.build: the existing Common__cpp custom_target now also takes Common.events.yaml as an input, alongside Common.errors.yaml, and emits event.cpp/event.hpp in addition to error.cpp/error.hpp.\ngen/xyz/openbmc_project/meson.build: added Common.events.yaml as an input to the markdown target, and added a new Common__registry custom_target that runs the registry command against Common.events.yaml to produce Common.json, installed under inst_registry_dir.\n\nCould you point me to how this event/error should be wired up to the Client interface\n(https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/e5cafef0032e7b7e93624ea8642f06a56b14bf35/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Network/Client/Create.interface.yaml#L15)\nso it\u0027s actually caught and returned as a D-Bus error reply?\n\nIs it declared under the errors: list of the specific method (Create) that throws it, same as with Common.errors.yaml-based errors, or does the events/registry path expect something different?",
